"NO ME HE IDO.

Cerca, bien cerca.
Estoy... en algún lugar estoy.
No puedes tocarme asi como no se puede tocar el amor... pero si puedes sentirlo.

Estoy en la sonrisa de tu recuerdo.
Estoy en el silencio de tu suspiro.
Estoy en la carita de quien ha nacido.
¿Escuchas el eco que se produce cuando ríes? 
Ese soy yo. 
Estoy, creeme que estoy.
No tan lejos. No me busques tan lejos.
Estoy cerca, bien cerca, a tu lado.

description: 8.9m Posts - See Instagram photos and videos from ‘pumpkin’ hashtag
caption:
"#Halloween is officially over, but don’t trash your #pumpkins! There are several ways to recycle them with #wildlife and your #garden in mind. (Please keep in mind this applies to non-painted pumpkins, as the toxins in paint can be harmful to wildlife.) 1. Compost your pumpkins. If you’ve carved a jack-o-lantern, it may already be decomposing. Pumpkins are 90% water, which means they easily and quickly break down. This makes them a great addition to your compost pile. Prevent unwanted #pumpkin plants by removing the seeds first (set seeds aside for #2 and #4). If you don’t have a compost bin or pile, check your local government, nearby farms, or community gardens to see if they collect old pumpkins.

2. Leave seeds for wildlife. Large #birds and small #mammals will eat pumpkin seeds if you offer them in your #yard. Collect seeds from your pumpkins, before composting them, and let the seeds dry. Please don’t add salt or seasoning. Place seeds on a flat surface, tray, shallow bowl, or mix in with existing bird seed in your garden.

4. Cut it into pieces for #animals. Many backyard animals will eat pieces of pumpkin flesh. You can cut it into pieces and leave it out. 
5. Plant pumpkin seeds. The squash bee is one of many insects to pollinate pumpkin flowers. If you have room in your yard, you can save seeds for a harvest of pumpkins next year.", "comments": {"count": 0

caption: "#tbt to last year when I was #marielaveau for #halloween. What an amazing time of year where many traditions honor their ancestors from #diadelosmuertos to #samhain. I love thanking the ancestors for all that we are today and we still have a ways to go in terms of evolving.  Be safe and gentle my friends.  Look up Marie Laveau! Now Angela Bassett played her so dope in American horror story! But look up how she helped the community.  She was a strong woman who bore many children.  She helped a lot of women with fertility issues and other health issues.  She was an advocate for children and took care of a lot of people.  She actually had her own home and was very wealthy at a time where creole/Black woman didn\u2019t have much in New Orleans.  She is definitely one of my favorite women in history to know about.  Her tomb is visited more than Elvis\u2019s is in Graceland.  She is significant and the more I learn about her the more empowered I feel as a woman who also likes to help as many people as possible.  Alright...good night .", "comments": {"count": 0

To make these No Bake Breakfast Tarts by @oatmeal_stories start by;

Combining 1 cup pitted dates, half cup oats, 1/4 cup walnuts and a pinch of salt in a food processor and then press the crumble into tart moulds before popping into freezer to harden.
You'll then need to mix half a cup of pumpkin puree with 2 tbsp Natural CO YO, 2 tbsp maple syrup and a 1tsp of pumpkin spice before layering on top of the crusts.

description: 8.9m Posts - See Instagram photos and videos from ‘pumpkin’ hashtag
caption:
"Here's a great recipe from our friends @vegan_punks for anyone looking to use up those pumpkin pulp. You can't go wrong with a tasty soup on a cold November evening. 
#Repost @vegan_punks ・・・
🎃 Happy Halloween everyone! 🎃 Here's one more #pumpkin recipe to use up those carved pumpkins, and trust us – it's the perfect winter warmer. It's a thai red pumpkin soup, makes at least 5 portions with just a half of a pumpkin, and is really easy to make. Here's the recipe:
•
Ingredients:
•
🌿 1.5kg roasted pumpkin (peeled pre-oven)
🌿 1 white onion
🌿 2 tbsp ginger
🌿 850ml veggie stock
🌿 4 tbsp red thai paste (we used @thaitasteuk – it's definitely #vegan)
🌿 1 can coconut milk
🌿 1 stick of lemongrass
🌿 Juice of 1 lime
🌿 1 tsp coconut sugar (or any other sugar you'd prefer)
🌿 2 tbsp olive oil
🌿 1 tsp coconut oil
🌿 Garnish with 1 red chilli and @oatly cream
•
Method:
•
🌿 Peel pumpkin and chop into chunks (all roughly the same thickness so they cook evenly)
🌿 Toss in the lime juice and olive oil and roast on gas mark 6 for 45mins (or until soft), check at 20 mins and turn
🌿 Prepare the onion and ginger while the pumpkin roasts and bash the lemongrass a little so it becomes fragrant
🌿 Fry the onion and ginger with a little coconut oil until the onion is translucent and it's all fragrant
🌿 Add the red thai paste and cook for a few mins
🌿 Add the pumpkin, stock, coconut milk and lemongrass
🌿 Bring to the boil and cook covered for about 20 minutes
🌿 Take out the lemongrass
🌿 Blend it all up in a blender or use a hand blender 🌿 Serve and garnish with some chopped red chilli and a swirl of Oatly cream
🌿 Enjoy! 👊", "comments": {"count": 0

caption: "On occasion of \"All Souls Day\" and retaining what's in season, I've made a recipe my grandma and her sisters from the Amalfitano Coast used to make: \"Cocozza e fasuli\" (=pumpkin \u0026 borlotti beans). I roasted 4 varieties of organic pumpkins which I helped grow at the Albany Garden Club I volunteer. I diced them into chunks and continued roasting them whilst I stir-fried garlic, red onion, fresh ginger, turmeric, cumin seeds and chilly. I then added the pumpkin and the cooked beans and added a mug of vegetable broth and a generous amount of freshly chopped parsley. I'm leaving it to settle on the hob ready to have later on and share with other volunteers of the garden club. \n#albanygarden #thealbanygarden  #cocozzaefasuli #borlotti #pumpkin #healthy #vegan #vegetarian #healthyeating", "comments": {"count": 0

caption:
"Sharing my pumpkin granola recipe again this year. I like to pour some unsweetened almond milk over it and eat it as a cereal in the morning, but you could also eat it dry or use it as a topping for yogurt. I hope you enjoy this as much as I do!

Pumpkin Granola (gluten-free, dairy-free, refined sugar-free)

Ingredients:
1 cup almond meal
1 cup gluten-free oats
1½ cup sliced almonds
1½ cup coconut flakes, coarsely chopped
1 cup pumpkin seeds
1 cup pecans, chopped
1 cup dried cranberries (unsweetened)
½ cup Medjool dates, coarsely chopped
½ cup coconut oil
2 Tbsp pure maple syrup (optional)
½ cup pumpkin puree
1/2 tsp vanilla extract
1 tsp pumpkin pie spice
1 tsp cinnamon
1/4 tsp all-spice

Instructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 275 F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper or foil.
2. In a very large bowl combine coconut flakes, almond flour, oats, dates, cranberries, pumpkin seeds, sliced almonds and pecans.
3. In a small bowl, combine the coconut oil, pumpkin, maple syrup, vanilla extract and spices.
4. Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and stir until dry ingredients are thoroughly coated.
5. Spread the granola in a thin layer on the baking sheet.
6. Cook for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes to prevent burning.
.

.

@chocolatecoveredkatie

1/2 cup pumpkin puree
1/2 cup melted coconut butter 
1/4 cup pure maple syrup 
1/4 cup cocoa powder
1/2 tsp pure vanilla extract
1/16 tsp salt
.
_________________________________

Line a small pan with parchment or wax OR have candy molds ready. Combine all ingredients until smooth—it’s smoother if you use a hand blender but can be done by hand. Just make sure the coconut butter is melted before starting. Smooth into pan, and freeze to set.

description: 8.9m Posts - See Instagram photos and videos from ‘pumpkin’ hashtag
caption:
"#ad Anyone who knows me knows that I love to bake!  When Fall season comes around I make a seasonal favorite for friends and family, Mini Pumpkin Salted Caramel Cheesecake with Gingersnap Pecan Crust.  Here’s the recipe:
Crust
1.5 cups ground gingersnap cookies
1.5 cups pecans
¼ cup brown sugar
¼ cup butter, melted

Grind together the cookie crumbs, pecans & sugar in a food processor.  Add the melted butter and mix well. Spray pan with non stick spray. Press mixture into mini cupcake and bake for 4 minutes at 350 degrees.
-
Filling
½ lb cream cheese, room temp
¼ cup + 2.5 T sugar
¾ cups canned pumpkin puree
⅛ cup whipping cream
¾ Tablespoon cinnamon
¼ Teaspoon nutmeg
2 eggs

Beat cream cheese & sugar together with a paddle attachment. Beat in the pumpkin, whipping cream, spices.  Add the eggs.  Pipe filling into the pre baked crusts with a piping bag until the hit the top. Bake for 7 min and then check to see if it needs more time.  Needs to be set and puffed up slightly.  Let crusts cool and then place in freezer until they are hard and can be popped out easily with a small knife.
-
Topping
1 lb cream cheese, room temp
¾ cup + 1 Tablespoon sugar
¼ cup + 1 Tablespoon whipping cream

Beat the cream cheese & sugar together.  Add in the whipping cream and beat until smooth.
Pipe onto chilled cheesecakes with a piping bag and tip of choice. Then drizzle with salted caramel.
-
Salted Caramel
1 cup heavy cream
2 Teaspoon salt
2 cup sugar
¼ cup light corn syrup
½ cup sour cream
½ cup water

Combine the cream and salt in a saucepan & simmer until dissolved.  Combine the water, sugar and corn syrup in a saucepan and cook on high until 350 degrees, ‪around 6-8‬ minutes

Remove from the heat and let cool for one minute and then add the cream to the mixture.  Whisk in the sour cream.  Let the caramel cool to room temp and then refrigerate.  In order to pop out eat mini cheesecake  out of the muffin pan easily without leaving left over crust, I use PAM Spray Pumps to coat my mini muffin pans so that each mini cheesecake can pop out easily.  I also find PAM Spray Pumps to be a neater way to coat a muffin pan.  @pamcookingsprayofficial #YouPAMDoIt #cheesecake #pumpkin #dessert", "comments": {"count": 0

caption:
"So out of all the pumpkins we chose the middle 2 to make meals out of first. 3 meals so far and still have some left!

No.1 = Pumpkin + prawn curry
Using, pumpkin/prawns, onion, garlic, ginger, turmeric, coconut oil (2tsp), lime juice, peppers, carrots, celery, red pepper, chopped toms, tomato puree and 2tbs of pataks madras curry paste, bit of tobasco sauce + dried basil = 8 syns overall but 4 syns split between 2 people.

No.2 = a yummy bbq bean and pumpkin soup I made up using, pumpkin, red onion, garlic, baked beans, butter beans, red pepper, pasata, smoked paprika, mustard powder, balsamic vinegar + a bit of tobasco sauce. Free of syns and sooo good! Vegan without the cheese!

No.3 = Cumin pumpkin mash with quorn sweet chilli sausages and mushroom/tomato gravy. Mash made with pumpkin, cumin, chopped parsley, 1 tsp of butter, tiny bit of balsamic vinegar, salt + pepper. DELICIOUS! 
Sauce made with red wine stock cube, mushrooms, parsley, tomato puree, onion (free)(Roughly 1.5 syns for butter and we think 2 syns each for the quorn sausages)

Roll on spaghetti squash tonight! Haha

caption:
"Właśnie robimy i polecamy bardzo prosty i smaczny przepis na ZUPĘ DYNIOWĄ Z IMBIREM I POMARAŃCZĄ.

SKŁADNIKI 4 PORCJE
500 g dyni, zważonej ze skórą
1 łyżka masła + 1/2 łyżki oliwy extra vergine
2 łyżeczki świeżo startego imbiru
szczypta imbiru w proszku
1/3 szklanki soku z pomarańczy
bulion jarzynowy
50 - 125 g serka Philadelphia (lub 80 ml śmietanki kremówki)
świeżo zmielony czarny pieprz

PRZYGOTOWANIE
Dynię umyć, usunąć pestki, obrać, pokroić w kostkę. W garnku roztopić masło z oliwą, włożyć imbir i delikatnie podsmażyć przez około pół minuty.
Włożyć dynię, szczyptę soli i smażyć mieszając przez około 3 minuty. Dodać imbir w proszku, wlać sok pomarańczowy i tyle bulionu aby przykryć dynię. Gotować pod przykryciem do miękkości przez około pół godziny.
Dodać serek lub śmietankę i przelać do pojemnika blendera. Zmiksować na gładki krem. Po zmiksowaniu sprawdzić czy nie trzeba doprawić solą.
PROPOZYCJA PODANIA
4 łyżki płatków migdałów zrumienionych na suchej patelni / świeżo zmielony czarny pieprz
Żródło Kwestia Smaku

1 cup almond coconut milk
1 scoop pure paleo protein
1 scoop collagen from @weareorganisource 
1 scoop Perfect fit (preferably their pumpkin spice flavor!) 1 tsp pumpkin pie spice
1 tsp agave
3 pitted dates
2 Tbsp Pumpkin Purée

description: 8.9m Posts - See Instagram photos and videos from ‘pumpkin’ hashtag
caption:
"Abychom Vás ještě více navnadili na naši vánoční edici mandlového másla s perníkovým kořením 😋, připravili jsme si pro Vás recept, kde je tohle máslo nedílnou součástí 🤐 Navíc se teď každý týden můžete těšit na nový recept na vánoční cukroví 🎄🎅🏻 Dýňové perníčky 🎃
➡️140g dýňového pyré (250g oloupané dýně hokkaido vaříme na středním plameni v 0,5litru vody 20minut, vodu slijeme a dýni rozmixujeme)
➡️2 vejce ➡️1 lžička skořice ➡️1lžička kypřícího prasku ➡️2 lžíce lifelike mandlove máslo s perníkovým kořením ➡️Vanilkové kapky ➡️50g kokosoveho cukru ➡️200g špaldové mouky hladké 
Poleva
➡️60g philadelphia sýr
➡️60 řeckého jogurt
➡️Vanilkove kapky ➡️Skořice 
Do vychladlého dýňového pyré přidáme vejce a promícháme. Přidáme skořici kypřící prášek, vanilkové kapky, kokosový cukr a nakonec vánoční edici Lifelike. Postupně přidáváme mouku. Na Pečící  papír pomocí lžíce tvarujeme kulaté perníčky (nám jich vyšlo 14) a pečeme na 175C 13-15minut. Vychladlé perníčky pomažeme směsí philadelphia sýra smícháného s řeckým jogurtem a vanilkovými kapkami. caption: "Before the time of everyone's favorite lovable  Jack Skellington or peoples creation of fear into the woods where the Slender man appears, there was a darker and heartless creature that lies in the darkest corners of Halloween \ud83c\udf83which this creature only awakens every Halloween and seeks the lives of people that feel loneliness in themselves and brings them to its world so it can live within people's hearts and saves them a special seat to make a deal with them and grant it for them \ud83c\udf83this creature that defines the actual nature of horror for Halloween is a scarecrow because they are creatures with emptiness and they don't have feelings for others. A scarecrow is more like an eater of worlds that preys on ones emptiness. This piece defines a lot of my depression and anxiety because when my depression is off the chart I start to lose sleep and picture or hallucinate things that are aren't there and It scares me the most everyday. This piece defines what my depression is and the things that I hallucinate from. Everyone has their own demon behind their backs and they wait for the perfect moment to take them into the darkest part of a different world.
